{
  "stem": "15396.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I-- I had a friend named William Holland.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And his mother had been related to the Stulpnagel family.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were Germans and Americans of course.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was very educated and very interesting, spoke perfect German, looked German.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the only place in Paris that you had a decent meal, I guess it-- just after the occupation of the Germans was [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] where the German messes were, which they took over all the best restaurants and all.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he knew a few of the Germans.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He wasn't a bit pro-German or anything, in the sense of, you know, he wasn't in any way-- didn't agree in any way with the Nazis.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But he used to come back and tell me all the things that he had heard from them, knowing that I was going to pass it on to some of my friends who were in the French.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "What-- I didn't know what it was, but it was the underground.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And so we-- that's how I more or less got interested in that part of it.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then one day I ran into a woman whom I knew quite well, and had known her at parties and all.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we thought of her as a collaborator.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I didn't offer to shake hands or anything, which was very stupid of me because it meant that I wasn't, you know, that I was anti-Nazi.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And you didn't want to be anti-Nazi at that moment.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Obviously.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, can't remember.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I've got it written down somewhere in fact because she-- in an old address book, I found her name not long ago.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she's the one who told me about if I would marry one of the girls in the camp.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
